           SHORT="Limit a process's absolute execution time"

cat << EOF
imelimit executes a command and terminates the spawned process after a given time
with a given signal. A “warning” signal is sent first, then, after a timeout, a
“kill” signal, similar to the way init(8) operates on shutdown.
EOF
